The course begins with an on-site session where contemporary learning paradigm with its main components will be introduced. The course continues with independent e-learning sessions, where the topics will be elaborated using course study materials, recommended literature which will be reinforced in the seminars. The students conduct a micro-study to understand how to capture the elements of the new learning paradigm in learning situations. Students analyse the studied situations and, based on what they have learned, propose alternative innovative solutions that meet the goal.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The course provides a general and systematic overview of contemporary learning paradigm and its characteristic learning and teaching methods. In addition, it guides students to relevant scientific literature and prepares them to study and shape educational practices.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After completing the course, the student: (1) has a systematic overview about learning metaphors and its characteristic learning and teaching methods; (2) has a general overview about problem-solving, inquiry-based learning, collaborative learning, and self-regulation and reflection; (3) has skills to analyse and plan for apt learning situations.
